SP  - 153
EP  - 173
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/01/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(91)90082-O
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440769190082O
AB  - The Imhof procedure is used to calculate the exact finite-sample distributions of alternative heteroskedasticity robust Wald-type tests of scalar linear hypothesis in the normal linear model. The tests are distinguished by the variance estimator that they use. These include the White-Eicker and jackknife estimators. The calculations demonstrate the importance of regression design in determining the quality of conventional first-order asymptotic approximations to the null distributions of the tests.
ER  - 

