VL  - 47
IS  - 1
SP  - 47
EP  - 66
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/01/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(91)90077-Q
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440769190077Q
AB  - Multiple diagnostic procedures entail a partition of the sample space into a set of critical regions. When the procedure is designed in a piecemeal fashion these regions bear no particular relation to one another, and the procedure as a whole can be logically inconsistent. We use a simple example to illustrate these difficulties, and also to suggest criteria that should be satisfied by any diagnostic procedure that is to meet the needs of the practitioner.
ER  - 

